d Epigraphik\u003C/i> 206 (2018): 103–12\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/JQQKI6JP",{"type":165,"bibl":166},"discussion",[17],{"editor":168,"principal":171,"contributors":172,"change":180},{"_":169,"ref":170},"Jonathan Prag","#JP",{"_":169,"ref":170},[173,176],{"_":169,"xml:id":174,"ref":175},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":177,"xml:id":178,"ref":179},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":181,"when":182,"who":183},"renumbered files, uris and references","2021-01-19","#SS",{"n":102,"url":103,"height":104,"width":105,"desc":106,"surfaceType":107},[186],{"atLeast":187,"atMost":187},59,[189,190,191],"Bacci, Coppolino, 2009, La Necropoli di Abakainon: primi dati","Sofia, 2015, Abakainon. Nella dimora di Ade. La necropoli in contrada Cardusa a Tripi","Sofia, 2018, Nuove iscrizioni funerarie dalla necropoli di Abakainon",[193,194,195],"DX8AWC9Q","9QTE4E3Z","JQQKI6JP",[197,198,199,19,24,28,200,201,202,203,201,204,205,127],"isic004418","epitaph for [-?-], child of gerontios",{"_":5},"abacaenum","tripi","sicilia","sicily","necropoli di abakainon","ancient greek",[],{"title":208,"body":209,"divs":210,"editions":235,"images":245,"handnote":251},"ISic004418. Epitaph for [-?-], child of Gerontios","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ς̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Γ̣ερόντιου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>].\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>.ΕΡΟΝΤΙΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004418_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004418_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004418.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004418-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text based upon photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Sofia 2018: [-----]; a horizontal is visible above the final ου of line 2, which in context is surely the remains of a final sigma (the stone shows no traces of further letters to the right).\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Sofia 2018: [Γ]εροντιου; the foot of a vertical stroke is clearly visible before the epsilon, and the spacing is most compatible with Γ.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[?] (child) of Gerontios\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Interpretation of this fragmentary text is context dependent. The text/plinth forms a pair with the adjoining plinth \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004417\u003C/a>. On that second plinth, the genitive [---]εροντιου is legible in the second line. The only attested Greek name compatible with this is \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%93%CE%B5%CF%81%CF%8C%CE%BD%CF%84%CE%B9%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Γερόντιος\u003C/a>, which is known in later Roman times at Catania (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003199\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003199\u003C/a>) and Syracuse (\u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/H73GNMU6\" target=\"_blank\">Orsi 1896\u003C/a>: 31 no.318) - and the restoration of a gamma at the start of line 2 of the text presented here is the obvious resolution of the traces visible on the stone. Comparison with other examples of paired monuments in this necropolis, particularly \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004415\u003C/a>/\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004416\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004416\u003C/a>, shows that these monuments can record siblings. It is therefore all but certain that we can restore the name Γερόντιος in line 2 of both ISic004417 and this text, and that these two plinths also record siblings. In a few cases, including ISic004415/ISic004416 and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001208\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001208\u003C/a>, the first name is presented in the nominative: the traces of a horizontal at the end of line 1 visible on this stone strongly suggest a final sigma, which is most likely a nominative termination (although genitive forms are also possible).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Bacci and Coppolino 2009 113 and 166 tav.XXXIVa \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2015 113 fig.115 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 107 no.8 and fig.9 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Neat, regular, simply cut, widely spaced letters. Epsilon has shorter middle bar; rho has closed, regular eye; omicron is small and mid-line; nu is broad with verticals of equal length.\u003C/p> Line 1-2  59  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[211,214,217,220,223,226,229,232],{"id":212,"html":213},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ς̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Γ̣ερόντιου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>].\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>.ΕΡΟΝΤΙΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":215,"html":216},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004418_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004418_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004418.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004418-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":218,"html":219},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text based upon photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Sofia 2018: [-----]; a horizontal is visible above the final ου of line 2, which in context is surely the remains of a final sigma (the stone shows no traces of further letters to the right).\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Sofia 2018: [Γ]εροντιου; the foot of a vertical stroke is clearly visible before the epsilon, and the spacing is most compatible with Γ.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":221,"html":222},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[?] (child) of Gerontios\u003C/p>  ",{"id":224,"html":225},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Interpretation of this fragmentary text is context dependent. The text/plinth forms a pair with the adjoining plinth \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004417\u003C/a>. On that second plinth, the genitive [---]εροντιου is legible in the second line. The only attested Greek name compatible with this is \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%93%CE%B5%CF%81%CF%8C%CE%BD%CF%84%CE%B9%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Γερόντιος\u003C/a>, which is known in later Roman times at Catania (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003199\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003199\u003C/a>) and Syracuse (\u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/H73GNMU6\" target=\"_blank\">Orsi 1896\u003C/a>: 31 no.318) - and the restoration of a gamma at the start of line 2 of the text presented here is the obvious resolution of the traces visible on the stone. Comparison with other examples of paired monuments in this necropolis, particularly \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004415\u003C/a>/\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004416\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004416\u003C/a>, shows that these monuments can record siblings. It is therefore all but certain that we can restore the name Γερόντιος in line 2 of both ISic004417 and this text, and that these two plinths also record siblings. In a few cases, including ISic004415/ISic004416 and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001208\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001208\u003C/a>, the first name is presented in the nominative: the traces of a horizontal at the end of line 1 visible on this stone strongly suggest a final sigma, which is most likely a nominative termination (although genitive forms are also possible).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":227,"html":228},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Bacci and Coppolino 2009 113 and 166 tav.XXXIVa \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2015 113 fig.115 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 107 no.8 and fig.9 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":230,"html":231},"handnote","\u003Cp>Neat, regular, simply cut, widely spaced letters. Epsilon has shorter middle bar; rho has closed, regular eye; omicron is small and mid-line; nu is broad with verticals of equal length.\u003C/p> Line 1-2  59  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":233,"html":234},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[236,238,241,242],{"html":237},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":239,"lang":127,"html":240},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ς̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Γ̣ερόντιου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":237},{"id":243,"lang":127,"html":244},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>].\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>.ΕΡΟΝΤΙΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[246,248],{"image":103,"thumb":247,"title":106},"ISic004418_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":249,"thumb":250,"title":106},"ISic004418.jpg","ISic004418-thumb.jpg",[252],{"html":54},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Epitaph for [-?-], child of Gerontios\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n\t\u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic004418\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n            \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-09-10\">10.5281/zenodo.4022731\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-21\">10.5281/zenodo.4381944\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative\n                        Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\n                    \u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Tripi\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"site\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/186\">Necropoli di Abakainon\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\"/>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Plinth (support for a stele) with mouldings top and bottom, of the local sandstone; the upper part of the plinth is heavily damaged, with all of the upper portion missing and the left corner heavily damaged; only the lower portion of the text-bearing face is preserved. The plinth is the right one of a pair mounted on a single base, classified as an epitymbion of type C.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.inorganic.stone\" type=\"stone.unspecified\" subtype=\"unverified\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/75.html\">sandstone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.arch_element.plinth\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/1910.html\">plinth\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">29\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">49\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">63.5\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Most of the lower line of Greek text is preserved, centred on the front face of the plinth; traces of a preceding line are visible.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Neat, regular, simply cut, widely spaced letters. Epsilon has shorter middle bar; rho has closed, regular eye; omicron is small and mid-line; nu is broad with verticals of equal length.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Line 1-2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"59\" atMost=\"59\">59\u003C/height>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462062\" corresp=\"#findspot\">Abacaenum\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003Coffset>near\n                                    \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2522853\">Tripi\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003C/offset>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>38.05191, 15.10158\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0350\" notAfter-custom=\"-0201\" evidence=\"archaeological-context\">The tomb has not been excavated fully, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE, offering a terminus ante quem\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" xml:id=\"findspot\">Tomb 80 of the necropolis in contrada Cardusa\u003Cgeo>38.065190, 15.114380\u003C/geo>, where it remains in situ\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">Metcalfe 2016 visited site\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                 \u003Cchange when=\"2020-05-28\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created the file from template, publications, and photographs\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-09-10\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-21\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic004418_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic004418.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\u003Cunclear>ς\u003C/unclear>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cunclear>Γ\u003C/unclear>ερόντιου\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n               \u003ClistApp>\n                   \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>text based upon photographs\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                   \u003Capp loc=\"line 1\">\u003Cnote>Sofia 2018: [-----]; a horizontal is visible above the final ου of line 2, which in context is surely the remains of a final sigma (the stone shows no traces of further letters to the right).\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                   \u003Capp loc=\"line 2\">\u003Cnote>Sofia 2018: [Γ]εροντιου; the foot of a vertical stroke is clearly visible before the epsilon, and the spacing is most compatible with  Γ.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n               \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>[?] (child) of Gerontios\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>Interpretation of this fragmentary text is context dependent. The text/plinth forms a pair with the adjoining plinth \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\">ISic004417\u003C/ref>. On that second plinth, the genitive [---]εροντιου is legible in the second line. The only attested Greek name compatible with this is \u003Cref target=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%93%CE%B5%CF%81%CF%8C%CE%BD%CF%84%CE%B9%CE%BF%CF%82\">Γερόντιος\u003C/ref>, which is known in later Roman times at Catania (\u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003199\">ISic003199\u003C/ref>) and Syracuse (\u003Cref target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/H73GNMU6\">Orsi 1896\u003C/ref>: 31 no.318) - and the restoration of a gamma at the start of line 2 of the text presented here is the obvious resolution of the traces visible on the stone. Comparison with other examples of paired monuments in this necropolis, particularly \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\">ISic004415\u003C/ref>/\u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004416\">ISic004416\u003C/ref>, shows that these monuments can record siblings. It is therefore all but certain that we can restore the name Γερόντιος in line 2 of both ISic004417 and this text, and that these two plinths also record siblings. In a few cases, including ISic004415/ISic004416 and \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001208\">ISic001208\u003C/ref>, the first name is presented in the nominative:  the traces of a horizontal at the end of line 1 visible on this stone strongly suggest a final sigma, which is most likely a nominative termination (although genitive forms are also possible).\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Bacci and Coppolino\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2009\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>113 and 166 tav.XXXIVa\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/DX8AWC9Q\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                   \u003Cbibl>\n                       \u003Cauthor>Sofia\u003C/author>\n                       \u003Cdate>2015\u003C/date>\n                       \u003CcitedRange>113 fig.115\u003C/citedRange>\n                       \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/9QTE4E3Z\"/>\n                   \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Sofia\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2018\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>107 no.8 and fig.9\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JQQKI6JP\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
